WEBVTT

00:00:00.492 --> 00:00:02.132
(Child actors were accompanied by a guardian...)

00:00:02.132 --> 00:00:03.832
(and filmed in a safe, supervised environment.)

00:00:04.332 --> 00:00:05.632
- You know what this is? - Let go.

00:00:05.702 --> 00:00:08.572
- Let go. - You wanted proof? Here it is!

00:00:08.642 --> 00:00:09.642
Hurry up and take a picture.

00:00:09.702 --> 00:00:11.672
My gosh, this is ridiculous. Let go of my phone.

00:00:11.742 --> 00:00:12.942
- You think this scares me? - My!

00:00:13.012 --> 00:00:14.012
Let go, you jerk.

00:00:14.072 --> 00:00:15.512
I can't believe you pulled this. Seriously.

00:00:15.582 --> 00:00:17.582
I'm an expert. I can tell everything just by holding your wrist.

00:00:17.582 --> 00:00:20.952
- Let go of it! - What's this commotion so late?

00:00:21.012 --> 00:00:25.952
Officer, these people are trying to forcibly take our property.

00:00:26.092 --> 00:00:30.622
Your wife posted my picture online and started a rumour about an affair!

00:00:30.962 --> 00:00:34.732
- Listen, that's... - Wait. Let go, then we'll talk.

00:00:35.132 --> 00:00:38.102
The definitive proof is on this phone.

00:00:38.402 --> 00:00:40.602
We're pressing defamation charges. Got it?

00:00:40.672 --> 00:00:43.872
My gosh! Please. Go right ahead. We'll counter-sue for false charges.

00:00:43.872 --> 00:00:45.242
- Do it. Go for it! - Goodness.

00:00:45.312 --> 00:00:47.312
- Can you shut your trap? - False accusations?

00:00:47.372 --> 00:00:48.682
- You let go first! - Unbelievable.

00:00:48.742 --> 00:00:50.012
- You take your hands off. - Hey!

00:00:50.012 --> 00:00:51.312
Seriously, why you...

00:00:54.152 --> 00:00:57.352
All right, I'm taking all of you in. Let's go to the police substation.

00:00:57.422 --> 00:01:01.052
- The substation? Why us? - But they're the ones at fault.

00:01:01.322 --> 00:01:03.222
Why are you taking us in, too?

00:01:03.292 --> 00:01:07.492
Possible assault, attempted robbery. If you refuse to cooperate,

00:01:08.232 --> 00:01:10.062
I'll have no choice but to place you under arrest.

00:01:18.842 --> 00:01:21.342
I'm telling you, the proof is on that phone!

00:01:22.112 --> 00:01:25.752
- Are you sure? - That's why they fought so hard.

00:01:26.082 --> 00:01:27.412
Ma'am, let me see the phone.

00:01:28.512 --> 00:01:30.682
- Excuse me? - I just need to check it.

00:01:31.252 --> 00:01:33.192
If you continue to refuse, you'll only make things worse.

00:01:42.832 --> 00:01:44.832
(Police, Information)

00:01:46.672 --> 00:01:48.532
(Respect for Human Rights, Fairness, and Kindness)

00:01:52.342 --> 00:01:54.212
- What? - What's wrong?

00:01:54.212 --> 00:01:55.512
The photo...

00:01:56.282 --> 00:01:58.342
- It's not here. - What?

00:01:59.152 --> 00:02:00.452
That's impossible.

00:02:00.812 --> 00:02:03.222
- Keep scrolling. - Yes.

00:02:05.122 --> 00:02:06.152
It's really not here.

00:02:06.252 --> 00:02:10.262
All I see are pictures of food, flowers, and landscapes.

00:02:10.722 --> 00:02:11.922
See? He said it's not there.

00:02:12.592 --> 00:02:14.192
He says it's not there.

00:02:14.762 --> 00:02:16.132
Are you sure you aren't mistaken?

00:02:17.102 --> 00:02:19.272
I am absolutely speechless.

00:02:20.002 --> 00:02:21.602
But you were in Seoul today!

00:02:22.502 --> 00:02:23.502
Weren't you?

00:02:23.672 --> 00:02:26.372
I'm way too busy to have gone to Seoul.

00:02:26.672 --> 00:02:29.242
What? Do you want me to prove my alibi?

00:02:30.282 --> 00:02:32.582
Honey, she said she didn't go.

00:02:33.412 --> 00:02:38.282
- I'm telling you. I saw her. - You're wrong. You have bad eyes.

00:02:39.392 --> 00:02:42.422
Actually, that happens to me from time to time as well.

00:02:43.662 --> 00:02:45.732
I know you want to blame someone, but honestly.

00:02:46.592 --> 00:02:48.262
You can't just gang up on people like this.

00:02:49.002 --> 00:02:51.062
Part of me wants to demand an apology,

00:02:52.432 --> 00:02:53.632
but let's just leave it at that.

00:02:54.402 --> 00:02:58.072
Officer, are we free to go now?

00:02:58.372 --> 00:02:59.672
Yes, you may go.

00:03:00.642 --> 00:03:01.712
Have a good night.

00:03:02.012 --> 00:03:03.012
Unbelievable.

00:03:04.442 --> 00:03:05.452
Let's go.

00:03:13.152 --> 00:03:15.762
His family and my family...

00:03:16.092 --> 00:03:18.292
are sworn enemies.

00:03:18.892 --> 00:03:21.162
It's a blood feud passed down through generations.

00:03:25.472 --> 00:03:26.472
I see.

00:03:26.872 --> 00:03:30.272
Anyway, what's your real Korean name?

00:03:32.572 --> 00:03:33.642
My name.

00:03:34.912 --> 00:03:36.112
My name is...

00:03:37.282 --> 00:03:38.382
Yang...

00:03:39.482 --> 00:03:42.922
Yang, I know that much. What comes after?

00:03:48.622 --> 00:03:49.722
Hold on a second.

00:03:50.422 --> 00:03:51.462
Honestly.

00:03:52.192 --> 00:03:53.232
Woo Jae? What is it?

00:03:55.232 --> 00:03:56.232
What?

00:03:57.432 --> 00:03:58.532
What about Mom?

00:04:00.802 --> 00:04:02.642
Okay, I'm on my way now.

00:04:03.772 --> 00:04:07.442
Sir. Something urgent has come up, and I have to go.

00:04:07.512 --> 00:04:08.712
- I'm really sorry. - What?

00:04:09.382 --> 00:04:10.382
Darn it.

00:04:17.152 --> 00:04:18.582
- You're back. - Yes.

00:04:18.582 --> 00:04:19.992
Se Ri.

00:04:20.792 --> 00:04:23.062
Se Ri, you're the one who posted that photo, right?

00:04:23.492 --> 00:04:25.792
My goodness, Dong Suk. What an awful thing to say.

00:04:25.962 --> 00:04:29.332
Come on. I know it was you. Why hide it from me?

00:04:29.662 --> 00:04:33.002
Don't you dare repeat that. Don't breathe a word of this, okay?

00:04:34.732 --> 00:04:35.742
My goodness.

00:04:36.942 --> 00:04:40.142
What are you talking about, Auntie? What picture did my stepmom post?

00:04:40.242 --> 00:04:42.242
- I don't know. - Auntie!

00:04:42.312 --> 00:04:44.582
Didn't you hear him? I'm not supposed to breathe a word.

00:04:46.282 --> 00:04:47.582
Good grief.

00:04:48.082 --> 00:04:49.922
What's so interesting on that darn phone of yours?

00:04:50.182 --> 00:04:52.792
Go to your room. Can't you read the room?

00:04:53.292 --> 00:04:54.952
- Auntie. - I told you, I don't know.

00:04:55.352 --> 00:04:56.362
Seriously...

00:05:01.032 --> 00:05:02.532
That was a close call.

00:05:02.902 --> 00:05:06.472
I know. If I hadn't deleted it, we would've been in real trouble.

00:05:06.702 --> 00:05:09.072
I never imagined she would have seen me.

00:05:09.142 --> 00:05:11.942
Those people can never find out you were behind this.

00:05:12.372 --> 00:05:14.672
Don't worry. She'll just think she was seeing things.

00:05:15.742 --> 00:05:16.742
By the way...

00:05:17.182 --> 00:05:19.912
Was the studio apartment you were getting for Hyun Bin near there?

00:05:20.152 --> 00:05:23.282
Yes, it looks like her clinic is in that area, too.

00:05:30.392 --> 00:05:32.122
When on earth are you going to tell her who you are?

00:05:33.292 --> 00:05:36.632
I don't know. I'm not sure I even need to.

00:05:37.032 --> 00:05:39.472
I'm leaving in one year anyway.

00:05:39.732 --> 00:05:41.832
Didn't you plan on seeing her at all when you came back to Korea?

00:05:42.472 --> 00:05:46.142
I thought of seeing her from afar. Like during my military service.

00:05:47.742 --> 00:05:49.612
But you met her like this,

00:05:49.612 --> 00:05:51.612
and you even asked to move her to your office.

00:05:52.982 --> 00:05:56.552
I told you. I didn't have some ulterior motive.

00:05:57.052 --> 00:05:58.252
So, what's it like seeing her again?

00:05:59.052 --> 00:06:00.092
Do you still like her?

00:06:01.252 --> 00:06:02.262
It's just...

00:06:03.462 --> 00:06:04.622
It's nice to see her, I guess.

00:06:05.462 --> 00:06:07.862
I had a childhood crush on her because she seemed so cool,

00:06:08.492 --> 00:06:10.732
but I doubt that'll happen now.

00:06:11.232 --> 00:06:13.602
We're just coworkers.

00:06:15.532 --> 00:06:17.142
You never know.

00:06:18.402 --> 00:06:19.742
You might fall for her again.

00:06:29.122 --> 00:06:30.382
People are going wild, aren't they?

00:06:30.622 --> 00:06:31.782
Of course, they are.

00:06:31.782 --> 00:06:33.852
My husband had an affair and ran off.

00:06:34.092 --> 00:06:35.992
They all say I'm so unlucky because...

00:06:35.992 --> 00:06:37.622
my daughter-in-law is cheating, too.

00:06:38.222 --> 00:06:41.092
My gosh. People will say anything, won't they?

00:06:41.562 --> 00:06:44.362
I wouldn't feel so wronged if it were true.

00:06:44.362 --> 00:06:45.602
I know.

00:06:46.032 --> 00:06:49.572
Your husband is always in trouble and doesn't even make good money.

00:06:49.872 --> 00:06:54.112
You're so young and pretty. I wouldn't blame you for cheating.

00:06:54.312 --> 00:06:56.942
Mother! Someone will hear you.

00:06:59.182 --> 00:07:00.252
Ju Ah.

00:07:00.552 --> 00:07:02.322
Mom, are you really cheating?

00:07:03.082 --> 00:07:05.552
- Ju Ah. - Are you cheating? Answer me!

00:07:05.552 --> 00:07:06.592
Hey.

00:07:06.592 --> 00:07:09.922
Have you been drinking again? Will you be like this every day?

00:07:09.992 --> 00:07:12.532
Don't deflect, and tell me straight. Are you having an affair?

00:07:12.532 --> 00:07:14.162
Hey, seriously... Will you keep your voice down?

00:07:14.162 --> 00:07:17.202
Hey, Ju Ah, go on inside. It's late. Hurry up.

00:07:19.802 --> 00:07:21.772
Where do you think you're going? I asked if you're having an affair!

00:07:22.002 --> 00:07:23.002
Oh, dear.

00:07:25.202 --> 00:07:27.442
No! I told you. I'm not!

00:07:27.712 --> 00:07:29.312
Then what's with that photo?

00:07:29.782 --> 00:07:31.682
Do you know what people are saying in the comments?

00:07:31.942 --> 00:07:34.112
They say you're "Adultery Evangelist,"

00:07:34.112 --> 00:07:35.652
not "Love Evangelist."

00:07:36.922 --> 00:07:39.452
- Why, you... - My goodness. Hey!

00:07:39.852 --> 00:07:40.852
Hey.

00:07:41.122 --> 00:07:43.222
Why are you misunderstanding your mom like this?

00:07:43.292 --> 00:07:46.462
What misunderstanding, Grandma? Where there's smoke, there's fire.

00:07:47.892 --> 00:07:49.202
You've always been like this.

00:07:49.562 --> 00:07:52.432
You said you only married Dad because of me, right?

00:07:52.932 --> 00:07:56.702
You ignored Dad, mistreated him, and yelled at him over small things.

00:07:57.102 --> 00:08:00.042
Now, you're rich and famous, so you decide to cheat?

00:08:00.472 --> 00:08:03.342
- Is this why you moved out? - Hey.

00:08:03.612 --> 00:08:06.052
No, wait. Mom...

00:08:06.612 --> 00:08:08.112
Are you even really living alone?

00:08:08.412 --> 00:08:09.422
Ju Ah!

00:08:11.422 --> 00:08:13.992
The whole world can misunderstand me and curse my name,

00:08:15.222 --> 00:08:16.922
but shouldn't you be the one person who trusts me?

00:08:16.922 --> 00:08:19.492
You never believed in me. Why should I?

00:08:19.492 --> 00:08:22.502
Hey, get inside. Now. Go on, get in there.

00:08:23.902 --> 00:08:25.032
Have you been drinking?

00:08:25.702 --> 00:08:26.702
Have you?

00:08:37.642 --> 00:08:38.642
Really.

00:08:40.712 --> 00:08:43.482
Who on earth talks to their mother like that?

00:08:44.122 --> 00:08:46.792
What mother says such awful things to her own child?

00:08:47.192 --> 00:08:51.222
She always said she only married Dad because of me.

00:08:52.162 --> 00:08:56.902
Your mom was younger than you are when she said that.

00:08:57.502 --> 00:09:01.072
Why take to heart what she said when she was young and naive?

00:09:01.132 --> 00:09:02.942
Because it cut me to the core.

00:09:04.672 --> 00:09:05.842
Honestly, I just can't...

00:09:07.642 --> 00:09:09.012
Are you okay, Grandma?

00:09:11.012 --> 00:09:13.252
While your mother was raising you,

00:09:13.652 --> 00:09:16.152
I was afraid she'd regret quitting her studies,

00:09:17.052 --> 00:09:21.352
so I insisted on raising you myself. I barely let her touch you.

00:09:22.662 --> 00:09:25.862
And I wonder if that's why you never bonded with your mother.

00:09:26.462 --> 00:09:29.832
It breaks my heart every time you act like this.

00:09:30.902 --> 00:09:32.402
I'm sorry, Grandma.

00:09:33.302 --> 00:09:35.002
I know, I was wrong.

00:09:36.342 --> 00:09:39.872
Don't hurt your mom's feelings. You'll regret it later.

00:09:41.472 --> 00:09:42.842
I won't.

00:09:45.682 --> 00:09:48.182
- Get some rest. - Okay.

00:09:51.822 --> 00:09:53.492
Gosh, seriously...

00:09:56.562 --> 00:09:58.962
(Taehan)

00:10:06.172 --> 00:10:10.642
Mom. I was too harsh yesterday.

00:10:12.842 --> 00:10:13.972
Sorry.

00:10:14.042 --> 00:10:15.342
(Mom, I was too harsh yesterday. Sorry.)

00:10:15.572 --> 00:10:16.582
No...

00:10:16.642 --> 00:10:17.742
(Mom, I was too harsh yesterday. Sorry.)

00:10:18.712 --> 00:10:21.652
What was so harsh about it? It's not like I was wrong.

00:10:27.252 --> 00:10:29.492
Sorry, I'm late. I had an executive meeting.

00:10:29.522 --> 00:10:31.822
Why? Because of the product review and budget?

00:10:31.922 --> 00:10:33.262
Did they shoot everything down?

00:10:33.332 --> 00:10:35.492
Oh, well...

00:10:36.202 --> 00:10:37.832
The design team meeting is about to start,

00:10:38.362 --> 00:10:39.632
so let's talk about it then.

00:10:42.172 --> 00:10:43.202
That's okay.

00:10:44.202 --> 00:10:46.042
I hope everyone got home okay last night.

00:10:46.842 --> 00:10:49.182
Yes. It's a shame we couldn't stay out longer.

00:10:49.942 --> 00:10:52.752
How about we party all night at the workshop next week?

00:10:52.852 --> 00:10:54.782
- Yes, I love that! - Sounds great!

00:10:55.682 --> 00:10:57.952
And the proposal from yesterday...

00:10:57.952 --> 00:11:00.022
It was approved at the executive meeting today.

00:11:00.222 --> 00:11:01.452
- Nice. - That's awesome!

00:11:02.092 --> 00:11:03.092
The product review proposal...

00:11:03.492 --> 00:11:07.232
- and the budget increase? Both? - Yes. But...

00:11:08.392 --> 00:11:09.732
there's one condition.

00:11:10.862 --> 00:11:12.672
What's the condition?

00:11:13.832 --> 00:11:17.002
At the upcoming Korea Fashion Design Competition,

00:11:17.342 --> 00:11:18.702
we need to have a winning design.

00:11:19.042 --> 00:11:21.812
What? But isn't its deadline just around the corner?

00:11:21.942 --> 00:11:24.642
Gosh, we also have to prepare for the Hot Summer collection.

00:11:24.912 --> 00:11:26.912
So won't we be a little pressed for time?

00:11:27.952 --> 00:11:31.952
Use designs from your portfolios, past competitions, or reviews.

00:11:32.022 --> 00:11:33.752
I want you to use designs that were previously rejected.

00:11:34.422 --> 00:11:38.322
Submit a design you're confident in by tomorrow. The final selection...

00:11:39.462 --> 00:11:43.032
will be made by an internal vote from employees in other departments.

00:11:44.462 --> 00:11:45.832
- Okay. - Got it.

00:11:46.432 --> 00:11:47.472
Right.

00:11:47.732 --> 00:11:51.172
The winning design will be publicly credited to the designer.

00:11:52.142 --> 00:11:53.642
- It'll be credited? - Yes.

00:11:53.642 --> 00:11:55.812
The designer's name will be on the label.

00:11:56.182 --> 00:11:57.482
- Really? - For real?

00:11:58.342 --> 00:12:00.552
My gosh. What should I submit?

00:12:00.852 --> 00:12:02.252
What about your Metro Classic one?

00:12:02.352 --> 00:12:04.752
Where did I put it? Please tell me I didn't delete it.

00:12:25.942 --> 00:12:27.112
Is this one better?

00:12:33.752 --> 00:12:37.882
Wow, everyone's in full-on competition mode.

00:12:38.752 --> 00:12:41.752
I bet no one's going home or getting any sleep tonight.

00:12:42.292 --> 00:12:45.962
Is it really that big of a deal to have your name on your design?

00:12:46.862 --> 00:12:50.962
Sir, you really have no idea what you've started, do you?

00:12:51.032 --> 00:12:54.172
Not really. I thought it was only natural.

00:12:54.802 --> 00:12:58.542
I always wondered why clothes only have the brand name on them.

00:12:58.742 --> 00:12:59.912
That's exactly it.

00:12:59.912 --> 00:13:03.282
You've acknowledged the designer's worth.

00:13:04.142 --> 00:13:05.482
Is that how it comes across?

00:13:06.582 --> 00:13:09.652
Why else are designers so desperate to have their own labels?

00:13:10.822 --> 00:13:12.792
It's just a shame you don't realise...

00:13:12.852 --> 00:13:15.092
how truly exciting this is.

00:13:16.492 --> 00:13:18.622
I'll look forward to seeing your design, Ms. Gong.

00:13:18.922 --> 00:13:20.632
Yes. I'm looking forward to it, too.

00:13:22.032 --> 00:13:25.902
I'll design one with my name on it and have my grandma wear it.

00:13:26.072 --> 00:13:30.072
I'll finally take my mom, who looks down on me, down a peg.

00:13:30.142 --> 00:13:31.242
Yes!

00:13:31.972 --> 00:13:33.272
Gosh, which one is better?

00:13:46.092 --> 00:13:48.022
So, what's the update?

00:13:48.252 --> 00:13:50.862
For now, I've blocked the reporters' fact-checking calls.

00:13:51.622 --> 00:13:53.392
So we're not going to issue a counter-statement?

00:13:53.992 --> 00:13:55.832
No, I mean, no articles have been published yet.

00:13:56.162 --> 00:13:57.502
And it's not even true.

00:13:57.802 --> 00:13:59.832
If we put out a statement now, it'll just exaggerate the situation.

00:14:00.072 --> 00:14:03.272
Hey. What about the contract that's on hold?

00:14:03.442 --> 00:14:07.812
Oh, one of our writers had an idea for you and Jeong Han.

00:14:07.872 --> 00:14:10.082
We could film some content of you two getting along...

00:14:10.642 --> 00:14:12.712
and use that to open the show.

00:14:14.682 --> 00:14:18.752
We are getting along fine. We just see each other on weekends.

00:14:18.982 --> 00:14:20.492
Yes, I know. I get it, but...

00:14:20.822 --> 00:14:23.362
we have to think about the viewers. That's why we should do it.

00:14:23.622 --> 00:14:26.962
They believe whatever they see. Just look at what's happening now.

00:14:29.862 --> 00:14:31.802
I hadn't considered that.

00:14:32.972 --> 00:14:35.532
- Hello. Vote for number two! - Hello.

00:14:35.632 --> 00:14:38.072
- Hello. We're with Gong Jeong Han. - Hello.

00:14:38.142 --> 00:14:39.742
- We're counting on your vote! - For Candidate Number Two!

00:14:39.812 --> 00:14:41.442
- Hey, Dae Han. - Yes, sir?

00:14:41.512 --> 00:14:45.842
Gong's wife, the TV doctor. I heard she had an affair?

00:14:46.512 --> 00:14:48.682
What? Who told you that? Who? That's not true!

00:14:48.752 --> 00:14:50.482
I'm very disappointed.

00:14:50.582 --> 00:14:53.922
I'm not voting for Dr. Gong.

00:14:53.992 --> 00:14:56.362
No, I'm telling you it's not true! Sir, please.

00:14:56.422 --> 00:14:58.762
Seriously, that's not what happened, everyone.

00:14:58.822 --> 00:15:03.402
But I heard people say Dr. Gong is going to drop out of the race.

00:15:03.402 --> 00:15:04.402
That's not true!

00:15:04.402 --> 00:15:05.902
- Who's behind these crazy rumours? - What?

00:15:06.472 --> 00:15:08.132
Uncle, look.

00:15:11.972 --> 00:15:16.642
There she is. The source of these vicious rumours.

00:15:18.812 --> 00:15:20.112
I'm telling you. It's true.

00:15:20.412 --> 00:15:23.552
Everyone in Onjeong Market knows Dr. Gong's wife is cheating...

00:15:23.622 --> 00:15:26.082
You evil-tongued gossip! I will be sure...

00:15:26.152 --> 00:15:27.952
- to teach you a lesson today. - Hey!

00:15:27.952 --> 00:15:28.992
Hey.

00:15:29.052 --> 00:15:30.322
What are you doing here?

00:15:32.322 --> 00:15:34.492
- I will shut you up for good today! - Let go!

00:15:34.732 --> 00:15:37.032
Hey! You're disgusting!

00:15:37.362 --> 00:15:38.932
What are you talking about? I didn't spread any rumours.

00:15:39.002 --> 00:15:42.272
It was you! You're the one spreading lies!

00:15:42.332 --> 00:15:44.902
What lies? I'm just saying what's in the photo.

00:15:44.972 --> 00:15:46.342
- It's real? - It's real.

00:15:46.442 --> 00:15:48.872
Who would take such a photo and post it online?

00:15:49.142 --> 00:15:51.382
Yes, I wonder who could have done such a thing.

00:15:52.482 --> 00:15:54.612
- My stepmom did it. - What?

00:15:54.612 --> 00:15:57.182
So go ahead and sue her! I'll be the witness.

00:15:57.252 --> 00:15:58.882
Hey. Stop talking nonsense.

00:15:58.882 --> 00:16:00.622
It'll be chaos if the adults believe you.

00:16:00.692 --> 00:16:03.462
I'm telling you, it's true! For the doctor falsely accused,

00:16:03.462 --> 00:16:05.092
I'm making a noble sacrifice.

00:16:06.792 --> 00:16:11.002
My gosh. Am I not like a tragic princess?

00:16:11.202 --> 00:16:14.932
You know... Who was it? The one who betrayed her father...

00:16:15.002 --> 00:16:17.502
- and chose love instead. - Princess Nakrang?

00:16:17.772 --> 00:16:20.012
My, so she was a princess?

00:16:20.242 --> 00:16:23.112
No wonder I felt such a kinship with her.

00:16:23.742 --> 00:16:27.382
Hey, Woo Jae! Call Dr. Han already!

00:16:27.452 --> 00:16:29.922
Why don't you believe the words of a princess?

00:16:49.572 --> 00:16:52.072
It seems Woo Jae really doesn't believe me.

00:16:53.212 --> 00:16:54.412
In that case...

00:16:54.872 --> 00:16:56.982
I'll just have to take matters into my own hands.

00:16:59.882 --> 00:17:01.212
Sorry, who did you say this was again?

00:17:02.982 --> 00:17:04.452
Woo Jae's girlfriend?

00:17:06.082 --> 00:17:07.752
Woo Jae doesn't have a girlfriend.

00:17:08.722 --> 00:17:09.722
Who is this?

00:17:11.362 --> 00:17:13.232
Oh, Yang Dong Ik's daughter?

00:17:14.062 --> 00:17:15.292
What's this about?

00:17:16.162 --> 00:17:19.772
This is a very urgent matter, so I decided to call you directly.

00:17:20.102 --> 00:17:23.772
After all, whatever concerns you is my business, too.

00:17:25.102 --> 00:17:29.512
Dr. Han, about my stepmom, she really did go to Seoul.

00:17:30.282 --> 00:17:31.342
What did you just say?

00:17:31.642 --> 00:17:34.912
I'm saying, she went to Seoul to find an apartment for my brother.

00:17:37.152 --> 00:17:40.422
You little brat! What do you think you're doing?

00:17:40.492 --> 00:17:43.692
What? I'm just doing the right thing!

00:17:50.102 --> 00:17:51.702
This is driving me crazy.

00:17:55.372 --> 00:17:57.572
And she had the nerve to play dumb?

00:17:58.402 --> 00:18:01.042
Wait a minute. The coffee shop.

00:18:02.712 --> 00:18:04.512
Why didn't I think of that?

00:18:06.782 --> 00:18:09.652
- Honey. - You're back? And your patients?

00:18:10.652 --> 00:18:13.292
Hey, what's going on, everyone?

00:18:13.422 --> 00:18:17.422
Here, let's all watch this. I got it from the coffee shop.

00:18:27.772 --> 00:18:28.772
What is this?

00:18:30.142 --> 00:18:31.142
What's this?

00:18:36.512 --> 00:18:39.752
- What? - My goodness. Who is that?

00:18:39.952 --> 00:18:40.982
Unbelievable.

00:18:41.382 --> 00:18:42.382
- What the... - No way.

00:18:44.452 --> 00:18:45.452
What?

00:18:46.922 --> 00:18:48.492
- Unbelievable! - Oh, my word.

00:18:49.352 --> 00:18:51.322
- That's... - Good grief!

00:18:51.962 --> 00:18:53.592
Who is that?

00:18:53.692 --> 00:18:56.562
Mom, what do you mean, who? It's Bucket's wife.

00:18:56.962 --> 00:18:59.832
So after all this, that woman just played dumb?

00:19:00.132 --> 00:19:02.902
See? I told you there was no way I was mistaken.

00:19:02.902 --> 00:19:07.142
My goodness. How could she? She's got some nerve, hasn't she?

00:19:07.612 --> 00:19:09.682
- That jerk! I ought to... - Hey!

00:19:09.682 --> 00:19:11.712
- Jeong Han. - Dad!

00:19:11.712 --> 00:19:14.712
- Jeong Han. - Mom! We can't let this go, can we?

00:19:14.852 --> 00:19:16.682
I am absolutely not letting this slide!

00:19:16.952 --> 00:19:19.582
Of course. We can sue her for this, Mom.

00:19:19.582 --> 00:19:20.752
- This is a lawsuit. - Yes!

00:19:22.192 --> 00:19:23.522
What should I do, Mother?

00:19:24.092 --> 00:19:25.662
I'll do whatever you say, Mother.

00:19:34.002 --> 00:19:35.002
Welcome.

00:19:44.742 --> 00:19:47.512
I figured you wouldn't want coffee this late,

00:19:47.782 --> 00:19:49.312
so I ordered tea instead.

00:19:50.852 --> 00:19:52.582
I assume you know why I asked you to meet.

00:19:53.722 --> 00:19:54.722
Yes.

00:19:56.092 --> 00:19:58.392
When I found out that Eun Bin had spoken to you,

00:19:58.592 --> 00:20:02.032
I called the coffee shop to try and smooth things over,

00:20:02.662 --> 00:20:07.372
but they said you'd already checked the CCTV footage.

00:20:08.332 --> 00:20:12.872
- I was taking the CCTV to the cops. - Dr. Han, please.

00:20:13.312 --> 00:20:16.542
I may be sitting here right now,

00:20:16.912 --> 00:20:20.312
but in your mind, please picture me on my knees.

00:20:21.312 --> 00:20:22.312
Excuse me?

00:20:23.052 --> 00:20:26.522
If I were to actually kneel here, everyone would stare,

00:20:26.592 --> 00:20:29.222
and that would put you in an awkward position, Dr. Han.

00:20:31.192 --> 00:20:32.462
What game are you playing?

00:20:32.562 --> 00:20:36.562
I am truly, sincerely sorry, Dr. Han.

00:20:36.632 --> 00:20:37.732
Sorry for what?

00:20:38.502 --> 00:20:40.002
For taking that photo and posting it,

00:20:40.532 --> 00:20:43.032
for deleting it to destroy the evidence,

00:20:43.142 --> 00:20:46.072
for tarnishing your reputation,

00:20:46.942 --> 00:20:49.442
and for nearly destroying your career.

00:20:49.882 --> 00:20:51.142
At least you know what you did.

00:20:52.782 --> 00:20:54.152
I just really...

00:20:55.212 --> 00:20:59.422
wanted my husband to become Merchants' Association President.

00:20:59.792 --> 00:21:04.222
He could use it as a stepping stone to run for city council.

00:21:06.222 --> 00:21:07.992
As you know,

00:21:08.292 --> 00:21:11.432
I'm my husband's second wife.

00:21:11.932 --> 00:21:13.702
All the love his first wife couldn't give him,

00:21:14.232 --> 00:21:17.342
I want to be the one to give it all to him.

00:21:18.642 --> 00:21:22.542
I suppose if you can justify your wrongful actions with a motive,

00:21:23.512 --> 00:21:25.512
you think it'll feel less shameful. Is that it?

00:21:27.482 --> 00:21:28.482
Pardon?

00:21:28.552 --> 00:21:32.622
People who disregard moral standards to satisfy their own desires...

00:21:33.392 --> 00:21:37.792
rarely feel guilty, and their apologies aren't sincere.

00:21:39.862 --> 00:21:41.462
My goodness.

00:21:41.832 --> 00:21:44.732
Are you saying my apology wasn't sincere?

00:21:45.102 --> 00:21:48.332
No, that's not it. I'm completely sincere, Dr. Han.

00:21:48.432 --> 00:21:51.042
You're skilled at manipulating people's feelings,

00:21:51.102 --> 00:21:55.272
and you're more angry you got caught than sorry for what you did.

00:21:56.882 --> 00:21:57.982
That's not true.

00:21:58.912 --> 00:22:02.452
I'm really not that complicated.

00:22:04.152 --> 00:22:08.422
First of all, I've taken down all the photos and the post.

00:22:08.622 --> 00:22:10.462
And if you want to sue me for damages,

00:22:10.692 --> 00:22:13.662
I'm prepared to offer you a generous settlement.

00:22:14.162 --> 00:22:15.392
Well...

00:22:15.592 --> 00:22:18.702
Is there anything else...

00:22:19.262 --> 00:22:21.032
you might want?

00:22:21.602 --> 00:22:22.732
Like...

00:22:23.402 --> 00:22:24.602
withdrawing from the race?

00:22:25.472 --> 00:22:27.142
Is that what you're hoping for?

00:22:28.812 --> 00:22:31.742
Don't withdraw from the race.

00:22:32.382 --> 00:22:35.652
Winning by default just isn't my style.

00:22:37.152 --> 00:22:38.152
Oh, my.

00:22:39.182 --> 00:22:41.022
Thank you so much, Dr. Han.

00:22:44.362 --> 00:22:46.762
So, I guess that means...

00:22:46.932 --> 00:22:49.562
we've settled things today, right?

00:22:52.532 --> 00:22:53.532
Thank you.

00:23:04.482 --> 00:23:05.942
You forgave her, Seong Mi?

00:23:06.182 --> 00:23:09.612
I know, right? You should've torn her hair out.

00:23:09.882 --> 00:23:11.582
Seriously, are you just going to let it slide?

00:23:12.122 --> 00:23:15.222
Then what? Sue her and start a war? We live in the same neighbourhood.

00:23:16.092 --> 00:23:17.092
You did the right thing.

00:23:17.762 --> 00:23:19.192
Yes. You did the right thing.

00:23:19.522 --> 00:23:22.262
- You're staying for dinner, right? - Yes.

00:23:24.102 --> 00:23:27.672
Let's put this behind us and win fair and square.

00:23:28.072 --> 00:23:31.702
Wait, they're not playing fair, so why should we?

00:23:32.042 --> 00:23:33.172
I said to forget it, didn't I?

00:23:34.212 --> 00:23:35.542
Woo Jae, spare me a minute.

00:23:36.882 --> 00:23:37.882
Okay.

00:23:40.112 --> 00:23:42.852
I'm heading out. I'm going to go study for a bit.

00:23:42.912 --> 00:23:46.022
Honey, I'll come pick you up at the bus stop later. Okay?

00:23:48.592 --> 00:23:50.762
- Hey. - Yes.

00:23:54.732 --> 00:23:55.792
Jeong Han.

00:23:56.832 --> 00:23:58.362
Are you really going to play fair?

00:23:59.432 --> 00:24:00.432
No.

00:24:01.532 --> 00:24:02.532
I knew it.

00:24:03.002 --> 00:24:04.242
You're not going to let this slide, are you?

00:24:05.572 --> 00:24:07.912
- Of course not. - Right.

00:24:09.842 --> 00:24:12.312
- How dare they... - The nerve.

00:24:17.052 --> 00:24:18.052
Are you...

00:24:18.852 --> 00:24:21.622
- dating Yang Dong Ik's daughter? - What?

00:24:22.152 --> 00:24:23.592
No, Mom.

00:24:23.822 --> 00:24:26.862
This isn't the "You should study, not date" lecture.

00:24:26.932 --> 00:24:28.092
You're old enough.

00:24:28.792 --> 00:24:30.802
You can date whoever you want.

00:24:31.432 --> 00:24:32.502
Just not her.

00:24:32.762 --> 00:24:35.872
Did Eun Bin tell you? That her stepmom was behind this?

00:24:35.972 --> 00:24:38.402
And how messed up is that?

00:24:38.942 --> 00:24:40.772
Stay away from them, son. I mean it.

00:24:41.412 --> 00:24:43.242
That woman, Eun Bin's stepmother...

00:24:43.642 --> 00:24:45.782
Psychoanalytically speaking,

00:24:45.782 --> 00:24:47.852
her emotional responses are abnormal.

00:24:47.852 --> 00:24:50.522
To put it simply, she's a crazy witch.

00:24:51.352 --> 00:24:53.352
- Mom. - Don't you forget it.

00:24:53.452 --> 00:24:55.952
Seong Mi, I need a word with you.

00:24:56.692 --> 00:24:59.322
Yes, Mother! Remember what I said.

00:24:59.762 --> 00:25:00.832
Yang Eun Bin, you!

00:25:01.362 --> 00:25:03.332
Do you have any idea what you've done?

00:25:04.632 --> 00:25:06.332
And you just had to go tattle to Dad?

00:25:06.662 --> 00:25:10.842
Hey, how could you? I know you hate her, but come on.

00:25:11.172 --> 00:25:12.272
Aren't you one of us?

00:25:12.602 --> 00:25:16.312
Why wouldn't I be? She's the outsider, not me.

00:25:16.372 --> 00:25:18.882
- What was that, you little brat? - What? Am I wrong?

00:25:19.142 --> 00:25:20.152
Yang Eun Bin!

00:25:21.082 --> 00:25:24.582
Didn't I tell you I'd kick you out if you disrespected your stepmother?

00:25:25.082 --> 00:25:26.652
Dad, please, just go inside.

00:25:26.922 --> 00:25:29.222
I'll give her a stern talking-to, okay?

00:25:31.392 --> 00:25:33.022
Please go inside and get some rest, Father.

00:25:33.362 --> 00:25:35.092
We're just talking.

00:25:37.662 --> 00:25:40.372
Raise your voice one more time, and I won't let it slide.

00:25:43.172 --> 00:25:46.912
Happy now? Are you satisfied that the whole family is yelling at me?

00:25:47.772 --> 00:25:48.842
Unbelievable.

00:25:57.982 --> 00:25:59.822
Hui Gyeong? Birth control pills?

00:26:00.992 --> 00:26:04.192
My gosh, I just don't understand. Why would she do that?

00:26:04.622 --> 00:26:06.992
Apparently, she doesn't want to have a baby.

00:26:07.332 --> 00:26:11.432
What? Dae Han's wanted a baby for five years.

00:26:12.832 --> 00:26:14.402
That's what I'm saying.

00:26:15.632 --> 00:26:17.702
I was just so flabbergasted.

00:26:18.342 --> 00:26:20.772
You think it's about money?

00:26:22.212 --> 00:26:24.642
She said no. I already asked her that.

00:26:25.042 --> 00:26:26.512
There's no way that's true.

00:26:27.352 --> 00:26:30.382
She was asking me about every detail of my contract,

00:26:30.722 --> 00:26:32.422
and she keeps holding it over me that they had to move in...

00:26:32.422 --> 00:26:34.152
because they gave me their security deposit.

00:26:36.622 --> 00:26:37.662
You think so?

00:26:38.392 --> 00:26:40.992
Maybe she's just saying no, thinking it'll make me uncomfortable?

00:26:41.732 --> 00:26:42.932
That's possible.

00:26:44.332 --> 00:26:46.032
Oh, boy.

00:26:52.372 --> 00:26:56.142
Mom, I'll drive you and take the bus back.

00:26:56.442 --> 00:27:00.412
Why not come to my studio tomorrow and bring my things back here?

00:27:01.452 --> 00:27:03.152
Your things? What for?

00:27:04.022 --> 00:27:05.882
I'm moving back here.

00:27:06.382 --> 00:27:11.062
- I put my studio on the market. - What? Really?

00:27:11.222 --> 00:27:12.892
Seong Mi.

00:27:13.692 --> 00:27:15.192
Seong Mi, are you sure about this?

00:27:15.762 --> 00:27:18.802
The commute might be tough, but I'll manage.

00:27:19.402 --> 00:27:22.002
Hey, shouldn't you have talked to me about this first?

00:27:22.432 --> 00:27:24.742
And when have you ever talked to me about anything?

00:27:25.372 --> 00:27:27.772
I'll make sure to get every last thing.

00:27:28.572 --> 00:27:30.212
Hey, are you sure you'll be okay?

00:27:30.542 --> 00:27:32.412
My room will be too cramped. Right?

00:27:32.412 --> 00:27:34.412
And you need space to write your book.

00:27:36.252 --> 00:27:40.622
Dae Han, once the studio is leased, I'll give you the security deposit,

00:27:40.692 --> 00:27:41.952
so you can start looking for a place of your own.

00:27:42.252 --> 00:27:43.452
For you and your wife to move into.

00:27:44.862 --> 00:27:48.092
- Our own place? - Yes. You're newlyweds, after all.

00:27:48.362 --> 00:27:50.962
It's been weighing on me that you moved in because of me.

00:27:51.962 --> 00:27:55.472
Once your room is free, I'll use it as my office.

00:27:56.302 --> 00:27:58.602
Seong Mi, is this really because of us?

00:27:58.802 --> 00:28:00.102
It's for a number of reasons.

00:28:00.512 --> 00:28:03.442
I'm tired of people thinking we're separated or something,

00:28:03.612 --> 00:28:06.212
and I think I need to get along better with Ju Ah.

00:28:07.452 --> 00:28:08.752
I'm so sorry, Seong Mi.

00:28:09.752 --> 00:28:11.122
But I bet my wife will be thrilled.

00:28:13.952 --> 00:28:15.092
I don't know how to face you.

00:28:17.622 --> 00:28:18.662
Thank you,

00:28:19.992 --> 00:28:21.492
and you made the right choice.

00:28:22.792 --> 00:28:25.232
In a way, I'm kind of grateful to that family.

00:28:26.262 --> 00:28:28.702
I think we made the right call deciding to let it go, Dad.

00:28:29.072 --> 00:28:32.472
Grateful? I'm still furious with them. You know?

00:28:58.902 --> 00:28:59.932
All right, let's go.

00:29:06.402 --> 00:29:09.772
(The 16th Onjeong Market Merchants' Association Presidential Election)

00:29:19.152 --> 00:29:21.652
(The expert who knows Onjeong Market best)

00:29:27.732 --> 00:29:30.432
(The go-to doctor for Onjeong Market merchants)

00:29:30.602 --> 00:29:33.672
Bucket.

00:29:38.102 --> 00:29:39.242
Oh, shoot.

00:29:40.072 --> 00:29:44.282
- Hey, what are you doing? - What? Too childish for you?

00:29:46.042 --> 00:29:48.752
The more childish the revenge, the more it gets under their skin.

00:29:48.812 --> 00:29:52.722
- Look at this. Look. - I see it. But why that one?

00:29:54.792 --> 00:29:56.192
Come on.

00:29:56.922 --> 00:29:58.462
(Gong Jeong Han: A leader with empathy)

00:29:58.522 --> 00:30:00.562
Hey, what are you doing?

00:30:00.862 --> 00:30:02.662
You're supposed to draw on Bucket's face.

00:30:02.732 --> 00:30:06.862
Hey, if we draw on Bucket's face, they'll know it was us.

00:30:06.862 --> 00:30:09.102
- Right. - Bingo!

00:30:09.172 --> 00:30:11.542
A reverse-psychology negative campaign by self-sacrifice?

00:30:11.742 --> 00:30:12.872
You're a genius.

00:30:13.572 --> 00:30:15.942
- I have my moments. Hey. - Yes.

00:30:15.942 --> 00:30:18.582
My face. You got that, right?

00:30:37.362 --> 00:30:38.362
Perfect.

00:31:00.122 --> 00:31:02.152
(Number 2 Gong Jeong Han, Number 1 Yang Dong Ik)

00:31:02.152 --> 00:31:03.152
(Rude)

00:31:03.222 --> 00:31:05.362
(Toupee! He's bald!)

00:31:05.422 --> 00:31:07.832
(Onjeong Market)

00:31:07.892 --> 00:31:09.162
(Unnecessary treatments, phony, bald hypocrite)

00:31:09.232 --> 00:31:12.902
This is so unbelievably childish. Don't you think they went too far?

00:31:12.962 --> 00:31:16.202
I know, right? How could anyone take a handsome face like mine...

00:31:16.272 --> 00:31:18.442
and ruin it like this?

00:31:18.742 --> 00:31:22.942
- Isn't this illegal? - Yes, it is.

00:31:23.412 --> 00:31:26.782
Vandalizing a Merchants' Association poster is destruction of property,

00:31:26.912 --> 00:31:28.512
punishable by up to three years in jail...

00:31:28.512 --> 00:31:29.852
or a fine of up to 7,000 dollars.

00:31:30.252 --> 00:31:31.852
There's CCTV right here, too. What do you say?

00:31:32.582 --> 00:31:34.852
- Should I start an investigation? - No.

00:31:35.352 --> 00:31:37.922
That won't be necessary. Right, Jeong Han?

00:31:38.162 --> 00:31:40.262
That's right. You must be busy.

00:31:41.832 --> 00:31:45.202
- All right. I'll be on my way. - Take care.

00:31:47.102 --> 00:31:49.532
(Number 1 Yang Dong Ik)

00:31:52.972 --> 00:31:54.472
(The Devil of Onjeong Market)

00:32:03.482 --> 00:32:04.482
Excuse me...

00:32:06.282 --> 00:32:09.092
I can't just stand by and say nothing.

00:32:09.352 --> 00:32:12.592
- Yes? - He forgave you,

00:32:12.592 --> 00:32:13.932
but you aren't even sorry.

00:32:13.992 --> 00:32:15.692
How could you let things get worse?

00:32:19.662 --> 00:32:20.902
What is she talking about?

00:32:21.302 --> 00:32:24.072
To do that to someone's face...

00:32:24.142 --> 00:32:26.872
- That's just wrong. - What is this?

00:32:31.412 --> 00:32:35.912
This prank has gone too far, sir.

00:32:36.982 --> 00:32:38.752
You should give your children a talking-to.

00:32:43.022 --> 00:32:46.462
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

00:32:48.692 --> 00:32:50.502
What have you done?

00:32:51.032 --> 00:32:52.132
It wasn't us. What?

00:32:52.402 --> 00:32:55.932
- We didn't do it, Dad. - You pathetic fools.

00:32:58.802 --> 00:33:01.772
Tell her I am very sorry.

00:33:02.442 --> 00:33:03.672
- Yes, sir. - Yes, sir.

00:33:05.582 --> 00:33:07.952
- Dad. - No, wait.

00:33:08.782 --> 00:33:11.852
Hey, when someone lets you off easy, you should know when to quit.

00:33:11.922 --> 00:33:14.192
Have you guys ever heard of playing fair?

