00:52:16.962 --> 00:52:19.162
Gosh, I'm sick of this.

00:52:19.502 --> 00:52:23.432
By the way, I hear Bucket's son is back in Korea.

00:52:24.502 --> 00:52:26.702
Really? You mean Yang Hyun Bin?

00:52:26.972 --> 00:52:30.712
Yes. That woman was looking for a studio apartment for him.

00:52:31.112 --> 00:52:33.412
His office must be somewhere near my clinic.

00:52:34.582 --> 00:52:37.812
Then that must be close to my office, too.

00:53:01.002 --> 00:53:02.012
What?

00:53:03.012 --> 00:53:04.012
It's up.

00:53:05.642 --> 00:53:06.642
All right, everyone.

00:53:07.242 --> 00:53:09.682
Our submission for the design competition...

00:53:10.382 --> 00:53:12.922
Drumroll, please...

00:53:14.152 --> 00:53:16.922
It will be revealed in 60 seconds...

00:53:23.232 --> 00:53:24.232
Okay.

00:53:25.402 --> 00:53:26.402
All right.

00:53:28.132 --> 00:53:30.132
Our final submission for the competition...

00:53:32.172 --> 00:53:34.772
is Ms. Kim So Hye's design.

00:53:35.512 --> 00:53:36.512
Really?

00:53:37.142 --> 00:53:39.282
- Wait, me? - Yes.

00:53:39.582 --> 00:53:41.542
In second place, by a very narrow margin,

00:53:42.682 --> 00:53:43.682
is Ms. Gong Ju Ah.

00:53:44.552 --> 00:53:45.552
Oh, man.

00:53:47.152 --> 00:53:48.692
Congratulations, So Hye.

00:53:49.692 --> 00:53:51.862
Thank you all so much.

00:53:52.662 --> 00:53:53.662
Hey, now.

00:53:54.392 --> 00:53:56.362
Laugh or cry. Pick one.

00:53:57.132 --> 00:54:00.402
Wow, your name will be on the label for next season's line.

00:54:01.002 --> 00:54:03.702
My dad is going to be so happy.

00:54:04.032 --> 00:54:07.102
I've always wanted him to wear something with my name on it.

00:54:07.942 --> 00:54:10.042
Gosh, I'm so jealous.

00:54:10.842 --> 00:54:14.712
Should we have So Hye take the lead on the competition project?

00:54:14.912 --> 00:54:17.912
Well, I'll handle the colourways,

00:54:18.012 --> 00:54:21.222
and it'd be great if you all could divide up the flats for each item.

00:54:21.482 --> 00:54:24.422
You're doing the sweater and pants? Should I take the outerwear then?

00:54:24.492 --> 00:54:26.962
Yes. Ms. Gong?

00:54:27.392 --> 00:54:29.332
If you wouldn't mind, could you run the DTP test...

00:54:29.332 --> 00:54:30.392
on the outerwear fabric...

00:54:30.462 --> 00:54:32.532
and also source the trims and materials?

00:54:33.262 --> 00:54:34.262
Of course.

00:55:03.232 --> 00:55:04.232
Are you okay?

00:55:06.002 --> 00:55:07.362
No, I'm not.

00:55:08.972 --> 00:55:10.632
I'm not going to lie.

00:55:17.972 --> 00:55:18.982
Yes.

00:55:23.952 --> 00:55:25.282
I understand, Vice President.

00:55:28.892 --> 00:55:31.422
Looks like they found the culprit in the Home Shopping incident.

00:55:32.522 --> 00:55:33.522
Let's go.

00:55:37.332 --> 00:55:39.062
Tell Mr. Park Jun Hyeok to come, too.

00:55:49.042 --> 00:55:51.942
You think someone really did this on purpose?

00:55:52.512 --> 00:55:54.142
I'm afraid so.

00:55:55.582 --> 00:55:56.582
Who?

00:55:57.412 --> 00:55:58.412
It can't be.

00:56:00.252 --> 00:56:01.252
They're saying it was Kim So Hye.

00:56:03.792 --> 00:56:07.162
A staff member said they saw her swap out the clothes that morning.

00:56:07.362 --> 00:56:10.962
If we start disciplinary action, I'm not sure how they will respond.

00:56:11.362 --> 00:56:12.802
If word of this gets out,

00:56:13.302 --> 00:56:15.302
it'll be a huge blow to our brand's image.

00:56:15.902 --> 00:56:19.502
You can't ask me to forgive her, can you?

00:56:20.542 --> 00:56:22.972
Ma'am, I'll accept the disciplinary action.

00:56:24.012 --> 00:56:25.012
What? Why you?

00:56:25.342 --> 00:56:27.282
Because I'm also responsible for mismanaging my team member.

00:56:28.112 --> 00:56:30.652
- Isn't that why you called me in? - No.

00:56:31.552 --> 00:56:33.552
I'm leaving the decision on Kim So Hye's disciplinary action...

00:56:34.482 --> 00:56:36.122
to the two of you team leaders.

00:56:38.152 --> 00:56:39.622
It's not my place to decide.

00:56:40.892 --> 00:56:42.762
I'll go with whatever Ju Ah decides.

00:56:51.402 --> 00:56:52.402
Why did you do it?

00:56:53.042 --> 00:56:55.812
Have you held a grudge against me all this time?

00:56:56.242 --> 00:56:57.312
I'm sorry.

00:56:58.842 --> 00:57:00.582
I was just so desperate...

00:57:00.842 --> 00:57:02.682
Did you really think you'd get away with this?

00:57:03.652 --> 00:57:04.652
Yes.

00:57:05.922 --> 00:57:06.922
What?

00:57:07.022 --> 00:57:11.322
I've never thought of you as being desperate, Ms. Gong.

00:57:12.762 --> 00:57:15.662
That's why I honestly had no idea you were looking into it like this.

00:57:16.462 --> 00:57:17.762
I thought if something like that happened,

00:57:19.002 --> 00:57:20.802
you'd just quit.

00:57:21.862 --> 00:57:22.932
Why?

00:57:22.932 --> 00:57:26.442
You didn't major in design, and you have a medical license.

00:57:27.102 --> 00:57:29.612
You could quit, and you'd be fine,

00:57:31.042 --> 00:57:32.682
but this is all I have.

00:57:33.942 --> 00:57:36.952
I am so sick and tired of hearing that.

00:57:37.982 --> 00:57:40.622
You don't know how hard I've worked so I wouldn't have to hear that.

00:57:41.282 --> 00:57:43.092
You people are unbelievable.

00:57:44.952 --> 00:57:47.122
So Hye, for me,

00:57:47.362 --> 00:57:50.192
becoming a designer wasn't a choice.

00:57:50.192 --> 00:57:52.102
I wanted to be a designer so badly...

00:57:52.402 --> 00:57:54.162
that I gave up everything else for it.

00:57:55.772 --> 00:57:58.332
- I'm sorry. - And "sorry" makes it okay?

00:58:02.812 --> 00:58:03.812
Unbelievable.

00:59:03.172 --> 00:59:04.272
Ms. Kim So Hye.

00:59:04.932 --> 00:59:05.942
Yes?

00:59:13.442 --> 00:59:15.212
What was it you asked me to do earlier?

00:59:15.612 --> 00:59:17.982
The DTP test on the outerwear, and what was the other thing?

00:59:18.982 --> 00:59:21.052
- What? - Ju Ah.

00:59:21.322 --> 00:59:23.122
I can't remember what else you asked for.

00:59:24.592 --> 00:59:27.022
Sourcing the trim and materials...

00:59:29.132 --> 00:59:30.192
Ms. Gong...

00:59:33.102 --> 00:59:34.962
What are you waiting for? Are you going to work or not?

00:59:35.602 --> 00:59:38.472
Yes. I'll get right on it. I'll work my hardest.

00:59:48.012 --> 00:59:50.212
(Taehan)

00:59:50.382 --> 00:59:52.382
(Managing Director Pacundo Ignacio de la Cruz Yang)

00:59:58.252 --> 01:00:00.262
(Taehan Group)

01:00:05.832 --> 01:00:09.132
So you're leaving me here alone to go back to the design office?

01:00:09.902 --> 01:00:11.902
You don't need me anymore, Director.

01:00:14.842 --> 01:00:18.372
So what should I do with this place? A meeting room or design space?

01:00:19.212 --> 01:00:20.812
Whatever you think is best, sir.

01:00:22.312 --> 01:00:25.412
- I'm going to get going... - Why...

01:00:25.882 --> 01:00:28.382
did you let Kim So Hye off the hook? You should've just fired her.

01:00:29.792 --> 01:00:32.522
Then, as the competition's runner-up,

01:00:33.062 --> 01:00:34.922
the collection would've been released under your name.

01:00:37.132 --> 01:00:39.202
Because Kim So Hye's design was good.

01:00:40.362 --> 01:00:43.602
My design might not have even placed in the competition.

01:00:44.072 --> 01:00:45.432
It looked like a rolled omelet.

01:00:49.912 --> 01:00:52.112
I made the decision for the sake of the team.

01:00:57.182 --> 01:00:58.612
Even so, if it were me,

01:00:59.322 --> 01:01:00.852
I don't think I could've forgiven her.

01:01:03.892 --> 01:01:07.362
My mom was wronged very badly once.

01:01:08.362 --> 01:01:13.332
She forgave the one who defamed her and accused her of an affair.

01:01:14.462 --> 01:01:16.702
I couldn't understand how she could forgive them.

01:01:17.772 --> 01:01:20.602
But then, my mom told me something.

01:01:21.472 --> 01:01:24.572
"Forgiveness is about freeing yourself."

01:01:25.312 --> 01:01:28.982
"It's not for the other person, but to escape your own anger."

01:01:29.182 --> 01:01:31.052
"It's a way of protecting yourself."

01:01:34.252 --> 01:01:35.552
She sounds like an amazing person.

01:01:37.352 --> 01:01:39.922
I know. And even though I can't stand her,

01:01:39.992 --> 01:01:42.692
I want to be just like her, which is ironic.

01:01:49.302 --> 01:01:52.242
- I should get going. - Okay.

01:01:52.872 --> 01:01:54.872
(Taehan Group)

01:01:58.812 --> 01:02:00.582
- Thank you. - Sure.

01:02:13.622 --> 01:02:15.192
Way to fall for her again, Yang Hyun Bin.

01:02:17.832 --> 01:02:19.162
I shouldn't be feeling this way.

01:02:24.032 --> 01:02:27.102
- Here you go, Mom. - That's enough.

01:02:29.542 --> 01:02:32.882
All right, everyone. The election is finally upon us.

01:02:36.112 --> 01:02:39.452
You've worked harder than anyone, pounding the pavement on a budget.

01:02:39.722 --> 01:02:41.282
Come on, it's not over yet.

01:02:41.282 --> 01:02:43.652
Let's make a final push this weekend.

01:02:43.792 --> 01:02:45.192
- Let's do it! - Let's do it!

01:02:45.252 --> 01:02:47.462
- Let's have a toast. - A toast!

01:02:47.522 --> 01:02:50.292
- Great idea. - I'll lead the toast.

01:02:50.762 --> 01:02:54.262
To Gong Jeong Han's victory!

01:02:54.262 --> 01:02:55.772
- To victory! - To victory!

01:02:55.772 --> 01:02:58.772
Wait. You can do better than that!

01:02:58.902 --> 01:03:02.372
Come on! To Gong Jeong Han's victory!

01:03:02.442 --> 01:03:05.342
- To victory! - To victory!

01:03:05.412 --> 01:03:07.342
- Bottoms up! - Bottoms up!

01:03:11.712 --> 01:03:14.452
- Take small sips, okay? - Dad, this is so good!

01:03:17.122 --> 01:03:21.462
Dispatch, this is Mackerel. Do you copy? Over.

01:03:23.262 --> 01:03:26.732
We read you loud and clear. This is Cutlassfish, over.

01:03:27.632 --> 01:03:28.662
Roger that.

01:03:29.532 --> 01:03:31.632
(Information, How may I help you?)

01:03:31.702 --> 01:03:33.672
(We are here to help with anything you need.)

01:03:34.842 --> 01:03:36.812
Sector A, campaign routes are overlapping.

01:03:37.272 --> 01:03:39.042
Sector B, expecting heavy crowd congestion.

01:03:41.642 --> 01:03:45.012
I'm deploying to the final rally to prepare for any contingencies.

01:03:45.152 --> 01:03:46.752
Stay sharp out there.

01:03:50.152 --> 01:03:52.662
(Kim Chun Hyeon)

01:04:00.232 --> 01:04:01.762
(The go-to doctor for Onjeong Market merchants)

01:04:01.832 --> 01:04:03.972
(Number 2 Gong Jeong Han)

01:04:04.032 --> 01:04:06.172
(Number 1 Yang Dong Ik)

01:04:06.242 --> 01:04:08.242
(Number 2 Gong Jeong Han)

01:04:08.302 --> 01:04:10.272
(Number 1 Yang Dong Ik)

01:04:10.342 --> 01:04:12.242
(Number 2 Gong Jeong Han)

01:04:12.312 --> 01:04:14.242
(Number 1 Yang Dong Ik)

01:04:39.202 --> 01:04:42.172
Hyun Bin, can I please just live with you?

01:04:42.372 --> 01:04:44.942
I don't want to live with my stepmom.

01:04:45.012 --> 01:04:47.382
She's doing the best she can.

01:04:47.842 --> 01:04:50.282
Even when she makes bad decisions,

01:04:50.682 --> 01:04:53.882
I try to understand that she's doing it for our family.

01:04:54.952 --> 01:04:56.192
I don't understand her.

01:04:57.992 --> 01:05:00.992
Eun Bin. But you like her, don't you?

01:05:01.322 --> 01:05:05.162
You're scared of getting hurt because you like her so much.

01:05:05.232 --> 01:05:07.032
So you're pushing her away on purpose, right?

01:05:07.602 --> 01:05:09.802
No, you're wrong! What do you know, anyway?

01:05:14.672 --> 01:05:15.742
I hate you!

01:05:25.652 --> 01:05:26.652
There.

01:05:27.382 --> 01:05:28.922
All done with the workshop prep.

01:05:30.592 --> 01:05:32.292
I'm starving. What should I get?

01:05:33.522 --> 01:05:34.522
Pork cutlet?

01:05:35.592 --> 01:05:38.332
That pork cutlet place I went to with Yang Hyun Bin...

01:05:38.392 --> 01:05:39.732
I should go there. It's been a while.

01:05:43.302 --> 01:05:44.972
But wait.

01:05:45.602 --> 01:05:48.342
Yang Hyun Bin... He's back but hasn't even called.

01:05:49.312 --> 01:05:52.372
And his office is nearby, I think. I wonder which apartment he's in.

01:05:53.342 --> 01:05:54.342
Hold on.

01:05:55.082 --> 01:06:00.052
Come to think of it, He and the director are so alike.

01:06:01.322 --> 01:06:04.222
Okay, let's see. First of all, they both have the surname, Yang.

01:06:04.552 --> 01:06:07.692
They both studied abroad, their families are similar,

01:06:08.362 --> 01:06:10.862
they live in an apartment near my office,

01:06:11.792 --> 01:06:13.902
and their parents' house is also near here...

01:06:14.702 --> 01:06:16.202
Pork cutlet is my absolute favourite.

01:06:17.502 --> 01:06:20.742
Right, and they both love pork cutlet.

01:06:21.042 --> 01:06:23.512
- What else... - You look strangely familiar.

01:06:24.772 --> 01:06:26.612
He said I looked familiar, too.

01:06:27.542 --> 01:06:28.682
No way...

01:06:28.982 --> 01:06:30.812
Director, what's your Korean name?

01:06:35.052 --> 01:06:36.192
Yang Hyun Bin.

01:06:40.292 --> 01:06:43.992
(Love Pork Cutlet)

01:06:47.362 --> 01:06:49.062
This place hasn't changed a bit.

01:06:54.802 --> 01:06:56.742
- One pork cutlet, please. - Okay.

01:07:09.592 --> 01:07:11.122
I've decided to study abroad.

01:07:13.292 --> 01:07:14.522
I promise I'll come back.

01:07:15.962 --> 01:07:17.392
Don't you ever forget me.

01:07:18.162 --> 01:07:20.802
Yes. I'll remember.

01:07:34.442 --> 01:07:35.512
Liar.

01:07:36.752 --> 01:07:38.482
As if you were going to remember anyway.

01:07:45.122 --> 01:07:47.262
- Can I get some water, please? - Yes.

01:08:31.172 --> 01:08:33.872
(Recipe for Love)

01:08:33.942 --> 01:08:36.572
- I studied abroad and never called. - Why?

01:08:36.642 --> 01:08:38.512
Because we were never meant to be.

01:08:38.512 --> 01:08:40.282
What? Are your families feuding?

01:08:40.282 --> 01:08:41.512
- Yes. - What?

01:08:42.512 --> 01:08:43.952
- One more time. - One more time.

01:08:44.012 --> 01:08:47.522
- We prescribe... - Love!

01:08:47.582 --> 01:08:50.252
Hello, everyone.

01:08:50.322 --> 01:08:53.892
- Bucket's son had a crush on you. - You knew?

01:08:54.022 --> 01:08:57.062
Marriage is never something you get to decide for yourself.

01:08:57.862 --> 01:09:01.132
- We'll begin the election vote... - Move.

01:09:01.202 --> 01:09:03.602
for the 16th President of the Onjeong Merchants' Association.